# Game data (Nexon is source of truth)

- **Official library (verify names, skills, modules, wording):**  
  - Descendants: https://tfd.nexon.com/en/library/descendants  
  - Weapons: https://tfd.nexon.com/en/library/weapons  
  - Modules: https://tfd.nexon.com/en/library/modules  

- **Machine-readable feed (what this repo uses — same data):**  
  `https://open.api.nexon.com/static/tfd/meta/en/` — e.g. `descendant.json`, `weapon.json`, `module.json`, `stat.json`.

- **Runtime catalog:** `GET /api/nexon/catalog/descendants|weapons|modules` serves the same compact JSON as `/public/data/*.json` (transforms live in **`src/lib/nexon-catalog-transform.ts`**). Client code falls back to static files if Nexon is down.

- **Do not invent** descendant names, skill text, module effects, or stats. When updating committed JSON: run **`npm run fetch:data`** / **`npm run fetch:stats`** (or **`npm run refresh`**) and read **`public/data/README.md`**.

- If the UI and Nexon’s site disagree after a patch, **trust Nexon’s library** and re-fetch; fix transforms in **`src/lib/nexon-catalog-transform.ts`** / `fetch-game-stats.js` only when the API shape changes.
